fields.body:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

<title>regex</title><script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/require.js/2.1.10/require.min.js"></script>




<style type="text/css">
    pre { line-height: 125%; }
td.linenos .normal { color: inherit; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5px; padding-right: 5px; }
span.linenos { color: inherit; background-color: transparent; padding-left: 5px; padding-right: 5px; }
td.linenos .special { color: #000000; background-color: #ffffc0; padding-left: 5px; padding-right: 5px; }
span.linenos.special { color: #000000; background-color: #ffffc0; padding-left: 5px; padding-right: 5px; }
.highlight .hll { background-color: var(--jp-cell-editor-active-background) }
.highlight { background: var(--jp-cell-editor-background); color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-variable-color) }
.highlight .c { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-comment-color); font-style: italic } /* Comment */
.highlight .err { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-error-color) } /* Error */
.highlight .k { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-keyword-color); font-weight: bold } /* Keyword */
.highlight .o { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-operator-color); font-weight: bold } /* Operator */
.highlight .p { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-punctuation-color) } /* Punctuation */
.highlight .ch { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-comment-color); font-style: italic } /* Comment.Hashbang */
.highlight .cm { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-comment-color); font-style: italic } /* Comment.Multiline */
.highlight .cp { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-comment-color); font-style: italic } /* Comment.Preproc */
.highlight .cpf { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-comment-color); font-style: italic } /* Comment.PreprocFile */
.highlight .c1 { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-comment-color); font-style: italic } /* Comment.Single */
.highlight .cs { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-comment-color); font-style: italic } /* Comment.Special */
.highlight .kc { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-keyword-color); font-weight: bold } /* Keyword.Constant */
.highlight .kd { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-keyword-color); font-weight: bold } /* Keyword.Declaration */
.highlight .kn { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-keyword-color); font-weight: bold } /* Keyword.Namespace */
.highlight .kp { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-keyword-color); font-weight: bold } /* Keyword.Pseudo */
.highlight .kr { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-keyword-color); font-weight: bold } /* Keyword.Reserved */
.highlight .kt { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-keyword-color); font-weight: bold } /* Keyword.Type */
.highlight .m { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-number-color) } /* Literal.Number */
.highlight .s { color: var(--jp-mirror-editor-string-color) } /* Literal.String */

/* Sibling imports */

/* Override Blueprint's _reset.scss styles */
html {
  box-sizing: unset;
}

*,
*::before,
*::after {
  box-sizing: unset;
}

body {
  color: unset;
  font-family: var(--jp-ui-font-family);
}

p {
  margin-top: unset;
  margin-bottom: unset;
}

small {
  font-size: unset;
}

strong {
  font-weight: unset;
}

/* Override Blueprint's _typography.scss styles */
a {
  text-decoration: unset;
  color: unset;
}
a:hover {
  text-decoration: unset;
  color: unset;
}

/* Override Blueprint's _accessibility.scss styles */
:focus {
  outline: unset;
  outline-offset: unset;
  -moz-outline-radius: unset;
}

/* Styles for ui-components */
.jp-Button {
  border-radius: var(--jp-border-radius);
  padding: 0px 12px;
  font-size: var(--jp-ui-font-size1);
}

/* Use our own theme for hover styles */
button.jp-Button.bp3-button.bp3-minimal:hover {
  background-color: var(--jp-layout-color2);
}
.jp-Button.minimal {
  color: unset !important;
}

.jp-Button.jp-ToolbarButtonComponent {
  text-transform: none;
}

.jp-InputGroup input {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  border-radius: 0;
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--jp-ui-font-color0);
  box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 var(--jp-border-width) var(--jp-input-border-color);
}

.jp-InputGroup input:focus {
  box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 var(--jp-border-width)
      var(--jp-input-active-box-shadow-color),
    inset 0 0 0 3px var(--jp-input-active-box-shadow-color);
}

.jp-InputGroup input::placeholder,
input::placeholder {
  color: var(--jp-ui-font-color3);
}

.jp-BPIcon {
  display: inline-block;
  vertical-align: middle;
  margin: auto;
}

/* Stop blueprint futzing with our icon fills */
.bp3-icon.jp-BPIcon > svg:not([fill]) {
  fill: var(--jp-inverse-layout-color3);
}

.jp-InputGroupAction {
  padding: 6px;
}

.jp-HTMLSelect.jp-DefaultStyle select {
  background-color: initial;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 0;
  box-shadow: none;
  color: var(--jp-ui-font-color0);
  display: block;
  font-size: var(--jp-ui-font-size1);
  height: 24px;
  line-height: 14px;
  padding: 0 25px 0 10px;
  text-align: left;
  -moz-appearance: none;

  height: 75%;
  border-radius: 50%;
  content: '';
  margin: auto;
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  right: 0;
}

<ul>
<li>\$  zero or one</li>
<li>*  zero or more</li>
<li>+  one or more</li>
<li>.   wildcard, will match anything besides a new line</li>
<li>(.*) match all text (greedy)</li>
<li>(.*$) match all text (non greedy)</li>
<li>\d  any digit</li>
<li>\D  and char</li>
<li>\w  letter, digit, underscore char</li>
<li>?   declaring a nongreedy match, or flagging an optional group</li>
<li>[a-zA-z0-9] match all lowercase and uppercase letter and digits</li>
</ul>

</div>

<h2 id="Search-Vs-Match">Search Vs Match<a class="anchor-link" href="#Search-Vs-Match">¶</a></h2><hr>
<p><strong><em>Use of re.search() and re.match() – 
re.search() and re.match() both are functions of re module in python. These functions are very efficient and fast for searching in strings. The function searches for some substring in a string and returns a match object if found, else it returns none.</em></strong></p>
<p><strong><em>re.search() vs re.match() – 
There is a difference between the use of both functions. Both return the first match of a substring found in the string, but re.match() searches only from the beginning of the string and return match object if found. But if a match of substring is found somewhere in the middle of the string, it returns none. 
While re.search() searches for the whole string even if the string contains multi-lines and tries to find a match of the substring in all the lines of string.</em></strong></p>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs  ">

<span class="n">current_date_str</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s2">%b%y"</span>

<span class="p">[{</span><span class="n">m</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]:</span> <span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">m</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">current_date_str</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">new_date_str</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">upper</span><span class="p">()}</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">m</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"(\d{1,2}(SEP|AUG)</span><span class="si">{1}</span><span class="s2">\d</span><span class="si">{2}</span><span class="s2">)"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">symbol</span><span class="p">)]</span>

<span class="n">String1</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'''We are learning regex with geeksforgeeks </span>
<span class="s1">         regex is very useful for string matching.</span>

<span class="s1">          It is fast too.'''</span>
 
<span class="c1"># Use of re.search() Method</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">search</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Substring</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">String1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">IGNORECASE</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="c1"># Use of re.match() Method</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">match</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Substring</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">String1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">IGNORECASE</span><span class="p">))</span>
 
<span class="c1"># Use of re.search() Method</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">search</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Substring</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">String2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">IGNORECASE</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="c1"># Use of re.match() Method</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">match</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Substring</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">String2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">IGNORECASE</span><span class="p">))</span>

<h2 id="Grouping-And-Capturing">Grouping And Capturing<a class="anchor-link" href="#Grouping-And-Capturing">¶</a></h2><hr>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">

     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># a(bc)           parentheses create a capturing group with value bc</span>
<span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"abc(123)"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"abc123"</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="c1"># the () just captures/returns those variables if the regex is a match</span>

<span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"abc(123)"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"bc123"</span><span class="p">))</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># a(?:bc)*        using ?: we disable the capturing group</span>

<span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"a(?:bc)*"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"abcbcbccdcdcdcd"</span><span class="p">))</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">

     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># matches a string that has either an a or a b or a c, -> is the same as a|b|c</span>
<span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"[a-c]"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"abcbcbccdcdcdcd"</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">findall</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"(abc)"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"abcbcbccdcdcdcd"</span><span class="p">))</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Greedy-and-Lazy-Match">Greedy and Lazy Match<a class="anchor-link" href="#Greedy-and-Lazy-Match">¶</a></h2><hr>

</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>The quantifiers ( * + {}) are greedy operators, which means they will match the longest string possible</p>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [28]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">regex_obj</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">compile</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"(Ha){3,5}"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">mo</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">regex_obj</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">search</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"HaHaHaHaHaHaHaHa"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">mo</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">group</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="jp-Cell-outputWrapper">


<div class="jp-OutputArea jp-Cell-outputArea">

<div class="jp-OutputArea-child">

    
    <div class="jp-OutputPrompt jp-OutputArea-prompt">Out[28]:</div>




<div class="jp-RenderedText jp-OutputArea-output jp-OutputArea-executeResult" data-mime-type="text/plain">
<pre>'HaHaHaHaHa'</pre>

</div>

</div>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">

<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h1 id="Look-Behind">Look Behind<a class="anchor-link" href="#Look-Behind">¶</a></h1><p>(?<=Y)X</p>
<p>In this syntax, the pattern will match X if there is Y before it.</p>
<hr>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [61]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="sd">"""</span>
<span class="sd">In this pattern:</span>

<span class="sd">(?<=\$) matches an element if there is a literal string $ before it. Since the $ is a special character in the regex, we use the backslash character \ to escape it. As a result, the regex engine will treat \$ as a regular character $.</span>
<span class="sd">\d+ matches one or more digits.</span>
<span class="sd">The following example uses a regular expression with a lookbehind to match a number that has the $ sign before it:</span>
<span class="sd">"""</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">re</span>

<span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'1 phone costs $500'</span>
<span class="n">pattern</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'(?<=\$)\d+'</span>

<span class="n">matches</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">finditer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pattern</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">match</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">matches</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">match</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">group</span><span class="p">())</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="jp-Cell-outputWrapper">


<div class="jp-OutputArea jp-Cell-outputArea">

<div class="jp-OutputArea-child">

    
    <div class="jp-OutputPrompt jp-OutputArea-prompt"></div>


<div class="jp-RenderedText jp-OutputArea-output" data-mime-type="text/plain">
<pre>500
</pre>
</div>
</div>

</div>

</div>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">

<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># lookahead</span>
<span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'1 phone costs 500$'</span>
<span class="n">pattern</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'\d+(?=\$)'</span>

<span class="n">matches</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">finditer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pattern</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">match</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">matches</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">match</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">group</span><span class="p">())</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>

    <span class="s2">"My name is Christopher Tao and I like Python."</span>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">regex_object</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">compile</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">'My name is (?P<first_name>\w+) (?P<last_name>\w+) and I like (?P<preference>\w+).'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">match_object</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groups</span><span class="p">()</span>

<h1 id=".finditer">.finditer<a class="anchor-link" href="#.finditer">¶</a></h1><p>loop through a string to find multiple matches</p>
<hr>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">re</span>
<span class="n">s1</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'Blue Berries Blue Berries Blue Berries'</span>
<span class="n">pattern</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'Blue Berries'</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">match</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">re</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">finditer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pattern</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s1</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">match</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">e</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">match</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">end</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">p_str</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'String match "</span><span class="si">%s</span><span class="s1">" at </span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s1">:</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s1">'</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">s1</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">s</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">e</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">e</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">p_str</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

     </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
